{
  "classification": "REPAIRABLE",
  "root_cause": "The proto-core substitutes a different sensitivity model for Lanners et al.’s propensity-weighted v/w model, then treats interval overlap as sufficient without enforcing observational-arm mixtures, outcome support, or constructing a common latent extension. Its comparator is therefore not the published statistic, while missing observational positivity makes m_{t,0} version-dependent. The inference class is additionally vacuous because an infimum over all measurable learners may select the true nuisances.",
  "directive": "Rebuild the angle around the published model. Let e_t(x,s)=P(A=t|X=x,S=s), mu_{st}(x)=E[Y|X=x,S=s,A=t], v_t^-(x)=mu_{1t}(x)/(1+gamma), v_t^+(x)=(1+gamma)mu_{1t}(x), w_t^-(x)=e_t(x,0)mu_{0t}(x)+e_{1-t}(x,0)mu_{0t}(x)/(1+rho), and w_t^+(x)=e_t(x,0)mu_{0t}(x)+e_{1-t}(x,0)(1+rho)mu_{0t}(x). State Lanners et al.’s exact comparator H_t=min(v_t^+,w_t^+)-max(v_t^-,w_t^-) and G_t^{LRVP}=E[H_t(X)], with published compatibility requiring G_t^{LRVP}>=0 separately for t=0,1. For latent-law feasibility, assume standard-Borel X, consistency, trial randomization, bounded positive outcomes [a,b], and uniform positivity of pi(x) and every e_t(x,s) in both studies. Introduce the observational missing-arm mean c_t(x)=E[Y(t)|X=x,S=0,A=1-t] with c_t in [a,b] intersect [mu_{0t}/(1+rho),(1+rho)mu_{0t}], impose the mandatory mixture q_{t0}=e_t(x,0)mu_{0t}+e_{1-t}(x,0)c_t, and require q_{t0} in [a,b] intersect [mu_{1t}/(1+gamma),(1+gamma)mu_{1t}]. Equivalently, clip the published w interval through the admissible c_t interval and clip v to [a,b]; call the resulting endpoints W_t^-,W_t^+,V_t^-,V_t^+ and define C_P(rho,gamma)=max_t E[(max(V_t^-,W_t^-)-min(V_t^+,W_t^+))_+]. Prove M(P,rho,gamma) is nonempty iff C_P=0. Sufficiency must use a measurable midpoint selector q_t from the interval intersection, recover c_t=(q_t-e_t mu_{0t})/e_{1-t}, and explicitly extend the observed kernel: in S=1 copy the observed arm-t outcome distribution to Y(t) in both assignment arms to obtain randomization and consistency; in S=0 retain Y(A)=Y and draw each missing potential outcome from an [a,b]-supported two-point endpoint law with mean c_t. Couple missing potentials conditionally independently, establishing one joint Q rather than merely armwise means. Replace the old witness by X in {x1,x2}, P(x1)=3/5, e_t(x,0)=1/2, [a,b]=[1/4,8], rho=gamma=1, with (mu_{00},mu_{10})=(4,1/2) at x1 and (4,4) at x2; then H_0(x1)=-2, H_0(x2)=3, so G_0^{LRVP}=0 although C_P>=6/5. Set mu_{01}=mu_{11}=1 in both strata, giving H_1=3/4, so the published armwise comparator accepts while exact feasibility fails. Demote rho=gamma=0 equality to a sanity corollary. Define C_P first as an observed-law functional, independently of estimation. For inference, specify foldwise series-logit learners for pi and e_t(.,s) and bounded least-squares series learners for mu_{st}, with compact X, covariate density bounded above and away from zero, uniformly bounded Hölder-beta nuisance balls, beta>d/2, deterministic basis dimension K_n satisfying K_n log n/n=o(1), K_n^{-beta/d}=o(n^{-1/4}), uniformly bounded/truncated fits, and foldwise uniform L2 rates whose relevant mu-by-propensity products are o(n^{-1/2}); give VC-type entropy and variance/nondegeneracy conditions for the score class. Use cross-fitted orthogonal scores with inputs (hat pi, hat e_t(.,s), hat mu_{st}) and a numerical directional-delta/contact-set multiplier bootstrap that permits positive-mass endpoint and arm ties. State uniform coverage and the local separation problem only over this primitive law class, never through an infimum over unrestricted learners.",
  "faithfulness_check": "This repair preserves Lanners et al.’s rho/gamma meanings, propensity-weighted v/w envelopes, and their actual average-overlap comparator. Observational positivity, support clipping, measurable disintegration, and mixture identities are well-posedness requirements; none assumes interval intersection or latent compatibility. The Hölder, series-rate, entropy, and covariance conditions restrict estimability rather than encode the zero set. Thus the honest field-tier kernel is the strict no-cancellation characterization and counterexample, not the already-known zero-sensitivity reduction.",
  "source_receipts": [
    {"source":"Lanners, Rudin, Volfovsky, and Parikh, Data Fusion for Partial Identification of Causal Effects, NeurIPS 2025","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC13196892/","receipt":"Section 4 defines gamma through the experimental v envelope and rho through the observational propensity-weighted w envelope; Lemma 1 intersects their lower and upper bounds."},
    {"source":"Published appendix compatibility discussion","url":"https://openreview.net/pdf/483d186f55b0f11a658d44df9df48f1655125b1e.pdf","receipt":"Appendix D defines G(t)=E[min{v(gamma),w(rho)}-max{v(-gamma),w(-rho)}], tests G(t)>=0 separately by treatment arm, and acknowledges that pointwise checking is replaced by average overlap."},
    {"source":"arXiv record 2505.24296","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.24296","receipt":"Confirms the paper, authors, sensitivity-analysis objective, partial-identification bounds, doubly robust estimation, and 2025 publication record."}
  ]
}

{
  "classification": "REPAIRABLE_IN_ONE_FINAL_ANGLE_0_REVISION",
  "root_cause": "The defects are representation, result-classification, and literature-positioning failures rather than a fatal mathematical defect. The exact common-extension iff is the central unproved kernel and therefore belongs as the headline Conjecture, while its necessity direction, mixture identity, cancellation witness, and zero-sensitivity algebra can remain proved supporting results. The clean Q/Y formulation is to keep Q on (X,S,A,Y(0),Y(1)), define the observed outcome as Y(A), and require the pushforward law Q_{X,S,A,Y(A)}=P; a separate Q-consistency assumption is then redundant. Hong and Li (2018) is missing as the direct numerical-delta comparator. A separate artifact inconsistency also exists: the supplied proposal.tex is an unfilled skeleton despite the reviewer reporting completed content, so v5 must regenerate and synchronize it with the corrected proto-core.",
  "directive": "Produce one synchronized v5 as follows: relabel thm:exact-compatibility, unchanged in target and substantive content, as headline Conjecture 1 (NOT YET PROVED); extract its routine necessity implication C_P(theta)>0 implies M(P,theta)=empty as a proved proposition derived from the observational-mixture identity and interval restrictions, and make the cancellation proposition invoke only that proved necessity result, never the conjectured sufficiency direction. Retain the zero-sensitivity statement only as an algebraic sanity check for K(P), without treating it as independent novelty. Define Q exclusively on (X,S,A,Y(0),Y(1)); replace ass:observed-extension and ass:consistency everywhere by the single pushforward condition Law_Q(X,S,A,Y(A))=P; propagate this change through the symbol table, latent-class definition, mixture lemma, conjecture statement, selector-based construction, proof route, scope flags, and every Q-marginal reference. Add HongLi2018, Han Hong and Jessie Li, 'The Numerical Delta Method,' Journal of Econometrics 206 (2018), 379-394, to the bibliography, related work, comparator table, inference-question gap, and proof route; describe its finite-difference numerical derivative bootstrap as one ingredient combined with Fang-Santos directional analysis, contact selection, and cross-fitted nuisance linearization, while explicitly retaining uniform tie-inclusive learned-nuisance coverage, testing, and local power as Open-ended Question 1. Regenerate every fixed proposal.tex section from this corrected proto-core, preserve the FIELD target, and do not add the optional sharp-effect corollary or any regularity, margin, contact-set, or bootstrap-validity assumption that would encode the open inference conclusion.",
  "faithfulness_check": {
    "headline_conjecture": "Structurally correct: sufficiency requires the measurable joint-extension construction and is the novel unproved crux. Calling the full iff a theorem would overclaim. Supporting results must not use the conjectured direction as if proved.",
    "q_y_consistency": "The pushforward formulation Q_{X,S,A,Y(A)}=P is the most precise repair. It preserves the observed Y coordinate of P, enforces consistency by construction, and avoids adding a redundant realized-Y coordinate or an extra causal assumption.",
    "prior_work": "Hong and Li (2018) must be credited for the numerical-delta mechanism, but neither it nor Fang and Santos establishes the proposal's learned-nuisance, positive-mass-tie, contact-set inversion result. That result must remain explicitly open.",
    "novelty_and_scope": "The repair leaves K(P), the exact compatibility conjecture, the cancellation witness, and the FIELD novelty floor unchanged. It neither claims that Lanners et al.'s pointwise inequalities are new nor pretends the inference problem is solved.",
    "artifact_integrity": "Because the supplied proposal.tex contains only TODO placeholders, acceptance requires a populated v5 consistent with the corrected proto-core; patching the JSON alone is insufficient."
  }
}

{
  "classification": "RECURRING_COMPARATOR_MODEL_DEFECT_BELOW_FIELD_FLOOR",
  "boundary_action": "CAP_BLOCK_RECURRING_DEFECT",
  "root_cause": "Angle 0 exhausted its ordinary revision cap at v5 while repeating a defect identified in the v1 root review and covered by a prior mandatory directive. The proposal still substitutes reciprocal lower endpoints mu/(1+rho) and mu/(1+gamma) for Lanners et al.'s published endpoints (1-rho)mu and (1-gamma)mu, so its claimed LRVP proxy, cancellation witness, compatibility functional, assumptions, and extension conjecture address a different sensitivity model. It also weakens the published trial assumption from joint randomization of (Y(0),Y(1)) to separate marginal randomization. These are foundational comparator-faithfulness defects, not localized notation errors, and the current LETTER assessment is below the locked FIELD floor.",
  "directive": "Block Angle 0 under the recurring-defect cap. Do not grant extra revisions, do not lower the FIELD target, and do not treat the existing witness or formulas as evidence about the published LRVP model. Any future proposal must enter through a new angle-selection cycle and establish comparator faithfulness from the outset.",
  "faithfulness_check": {
    "published_lower_endpoints": {
      "relative_nuc": "(1-rho) mu_{0t}",
      "study_exchangeability": "(1-gamma) mu_{1t}"
    },
    "required_parameter_domain": "rho,gamma in [0,1] unless a separately justified extension is explicitly distinguished from the published model",
    "support_clipped_endpoints": {
      "C_t_minus": "max{a,(1-rho)mu_{0t}}",
      "C_t_plus": "min{b,(1+rho)mu_{0t}}",
      "V_t_minus": "max{a,(1-gamma)mu_{1t}}",
      "V_t_plus": "min{b,(1+gamma)mu_{1t}}",
      "W_t_pm": "e_t(x,0)mu_{0t}(x)+e_{1-t}(x,0)C_t_pm(x)"
    },
    "required_trial_randomization": "(Y(0),Y(1)) independent of A conditional on (X,S=1)",
    "existing_witness_status": "Not faithful to the published model and therefore cannot support the claimed LRVP cancellation comparison without complete recomputation.",
    "retry_warranted": false,
    "switch_warranted_at_this_boundary": false
  }
}

